i18n Phase 2 (homepage + footer): SVG flags, translated copy, 9 locales

Replaces the OS-flaky emoji flags with vector SVG components and starts
translating the highest-value page chrome (homepage hero, menu showcase,
location, footer) across all 9 supported locales.

Flags
- Added country-flag-icons + components/i18n/Flag.tsx mapping each locale
  to its ISO 3166-1 country code (en→GB, ar→SA, etc.)
- Switched LanguageSwitcher trigger + dropdown rows and the
  LocaleSuggestionBanner CTA from emoji to <Flag> SVGs — crisp on every
  OS/browser, no more "🇬🇧" rendering as text on Windows
- Dropped the unused `flag` field from i18n/routing.ts LocaleMeta

Homepage translations (9 locales: en, th, cn, ja, ko, ru, fr, es, ar)
- messages/*.json now ship home.hero, home.menu, home.location and a
  prepared booking.* section
- HeroSlideshow: badge, headline, subtitle, description, slide aria
  labels, Reserve a Table CTA, prev/next aria labels
- MenuShowcase: eyebrow, title, description, Signature/From-the-kitchen
  tags, Explore Full Menu CTA
- Location: eyebrow, headline + accent, description, stat labels
  (Year-Old Trees, Above Sea Level, Avg Temperature), label/value/detail
  for contact cards (Location, Reservations, Email, Hours), inline
  Get Directions buttons
- Footer: brand tagline, Explore/Legal/Visit Us section headings, nav
  link labels (now reuse nav.* keys), Reserve a Table CTA, Open Daily
  hours line, copyright with ICU year interpolation

Booking page strings reserved
- Added booking.step_*, booking.field_*, booking.summary_*, booking.total,
  booking.continue_pay, booking.terms_agree in all locales. Component
  wiring intentionally deferred to a follow-up so this PR stays
  reviewable.
